l am not ashamed to have played the game, or now to have broken off from the sports. F or now, no one with envious eye disparages my pleasures, or poisons them with their dislike and envy. The villagers smile at me working over the turf and rocks.

You prefer to eat your daily allowance in the city with slaves, and are eager to be in their company; yet my shrewd body-servant here envies you the enjoy- ments of my woods and flocks and garden.
